Cell[BoxData["\<\"Case 1A is said to make \[GothicCapitalD] \
\\!\\(\\*StyleBox[\\\"separable\\\",FontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\), a product \
of functions purely of t and purely of r. Using \[ScriptCapitalA](t) instead \
of a(t\\!\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[\\()\\), \\(2\\)]\\) would have been more \
general yet, but it seems reasonable that if the curled spaces have any \
time-sensitivity that it would be due to the scale factor a(t). That is why \
we use it. Also, it is common in general relativity to consider A(t,r)=a(t\\!\
\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[\\()\\), \\(2\\)]\\), which is why we square it.\"\>"], \
"Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.978951926785626*^9, 3.981278886687457*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[1882]:=",ExpressionUUID->"54ad1d86-8889-486a-9458-7c57294ed1b9"],

